description:
## Context
pdf-gesture-handler needs to call ZoomStateManager for rebound filtering
and activity signaling.

## File
`apps/amnesia/src/reader/renderer/pdf/pdf-gesture-handler.ts`

## Changes Required

### 1. Add ZoomStateManager reference
```typescript
private zoomStateManager: ZoomStateManager | null = null;

setZoomStateManager(manager: ZoomStateManager): void {
  this.zoomStateManager = manager;
}
```

### 2. Add rebound filtering in handleWheel (~line 108-135)
```typescript
handleWheel(event: WheelEvent): void {
  // ... existing code ...

  // Add rebound filtering at zoom boundaries
  if (this.zoomStateManager) {
    if (this.zoomStateManager.isReboundZoomOut(newScale)) {
      console.log('[GestureHandler] Filtered rebound event at max zoom');
      this.zoomStateManager.signalOngoingActivity();
      return;
    }
  }

  // ... continue with zoom ...
}
```

### 3. Signal gesture end
```typescript
// When gesture timeout fires
if (this.zoomStateManager) {
  this.zoomStateManager.markGestureEnd();
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `setZoomStateManager()` method added
- [ ] Rebound filtering integrated in handleWheel
- [ ] Gesture end signaled to ZoomStateManager
- [ ] Console logs show rebound filtering at max zoom

## Quality Gates
- [ ] Build passes
- [ ] Rebound events filtered at 16x zoom
- [ ] Gesture end correctly detected

## Context
isViewportOnly is calculated fresh on every renderTiles() with no hysteresis.
Mode can flip between frames if user pans while zooming.

## File
`apps/amnesia/src/reader/renderer/pdf/pdf-page-element.ts`

## Current Behavior (Lines 723-725)
```typescript
const isViewportOnly = minTileX > 0 || minTileY > 0 ||
  (maxTileX + 1) * pdfTileSize < pdfWidth - pdfTileSize ||
  (maxTileY + 1) * pdfTileSize < pdfHeight - pdfTileSize;
```

## Problem
- Frame 1: Full coverage → isViewportOnly=false → full-page CSS
- Frame 2: Slight pan → isViewportOnly=true → viewport-only CSS
- Visual jump from CSS size/transform change

## Fix
Add hysteresis or gesture-awareness:
```typescript
// Lock mode during active gesture
if (this.isGestureActive && this.lockedMode !== null) {
  isViewportOnly = this.lockedMode === 'viewport-only';
} else {
  isViewportOnly = /* calculation */;
  if (!this.isGestureActive) {
    this.lockedMode = isViewportOnly ? 'viewport-only' : 'full-page';
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Mode does NOT switch during active zoom/pan gesture
- [ ] Mode switch only occurs after gesture settles
- [ ] Hysteresis prevents oscillation at threshold

## Quality Gates
- [ ] Build passes
- [ ] No visual jumps when panning at mode boundary
- [ ] Mode transitions smooth after gesture ends

## Context
Council mandated: Soft constraints during gesture, hard constraints at gesture end.
ZoomStateManager needs to support both constraint modes.

## File
`apps/amnesia/src/reader/renderer/pdf/zoom-state-manager.ts`

## Implementation
```typescript
interface ZoomStateConfig {
  // ... existing fields
  softConstraintFactor: number;  // 0.3 = 30% rubber-band resistance
}

// Add to ZoomStateManager class
constrainCamera(isGestureActive: boolean): Camera {
  if (isGestureActive) {
    return this.applySoftConstraints();
  }
  return this.applyHardConstraints();
}

private applySoftConstraints(): Camera {
  const { x, y, zoom } = this.state;
  const { minX, maxX, minY, maxY } = this.calculateBounds(zoom);

  let targetX = x, targetY = y;
  const factor = this.config.softConstraintFactor;

  if (x < minX) targetX = minX + (x - minX) * factor; // Rubber-band
  if (x > maxX) targetX = maxX + (x - maxX) * factor;
  if (y < minY) targetY = minY + (y - minY) * factor;
  if (y > maxY) targetY = maxY + (y - maxY) * factor;

  return { x: targetX, y: targetY, z: zoom };
}

private applyHardConstraints(): Camera {
  const { x, y, zoom } = this.state;
  const { minX, maxX, minY, maxY } = this.calculateBounds(zoom);

  return {
    x: Math.max(minX, Math.min(maxX, x)),
    y: Math.max(minY, Math.min(maxY, y)),
    z: zoom
  };
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `constrainCamera(isGestureActive)` routes to correct constraint mode
- [ ] Soft constraints allow rubber-band effect (30% resistance)
- [ ] Hard constraints clamp to exact bounds
- [ ] Bounds calculation respects current zoom level

## Quality Gates
- [ ] Build passes
- [ ] Rubber-band effect visible when panning past edges during gesture
- [ ] Camera snaps to bounds after gesture ends

## Context
Replace ZoomOrchestrator usage with ZoomStateManager in pdf-infinite-canvas.ts.
This is the main wiring task that connects ZoomStateManager to the rendering pipeline.

## File
`apps/amnesia/src/reader/renderer/pdf/pdf-infinite-canvas.ts`

## Changes Required

### 1. Replace ZoomOrchestrator instantiation (~line 445-460)
```typescript
// BEFORE
this.zoomStateMachine = new ZoomOrchestrator({...});

// AFTER
this.zoomStateManager = getZoomStateManager() ?? createZoomStateManager({
  minZoom: this.cameraConstraints.minZoom,
  maxZoom: this.cameraConstraints.maxZoom,
  pixelRatio: window.devicePixelRatio || 2,
  softConstraintFactor: 0.3,
});
```

### 2. Replace onZoomGesture calls (~line 4068-4091)
```typescript
// BEFORE
this.zoomStateMachine.onZoomGesture(zoom, this.getFocalPoint());

// AFTER
this.zoomStateManager.onZoomGesture(zoom, this.getFocalPoint());
```

### 3. Replace epoch/renderVersion usage
```typescript
// BEFORE
++this.renderVersion;

// AFTER
// Epoch auto-increments in ZoomStateManager.onZoomGesture()
const epoch = this.zoomStateManager.getEpoch();
```

### 4. Subscribe to state changes for CSS transforms
```typescript
this.zoomStateManager.subscribe((state) => {
  this.camera = { x: state.position.x, y: state.position.y, z: state.zoom };
  this.applyTransform();
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] ZoomStateManager instantiated on canvas init
- [ ] All `zoomStateMachine` references replaced with `zoomStateManager`
- [ ] Epoch read from `zoomStateManager.getEpoch()`
- [ ] Camera state synced via subscription
- [ ] No TypeScript errors

## Quality Gates
- [ ] Build passes
- [ ] Zoom gestures work correctly
- [ ] Epoch validation works
- [ ] No state desync during rapid zoom

## Context
LLM Council approved Two-Track Pipeline architecture with graceful degradation.

Current behavior rejects ALL tiles with epoch mismatch → blank screens during zoom.
New behavior: Skip stale tiles, keep existing content visible.

## File
`apps/amnesia/src/reader/renderer/pdf/pdf-page-element.ts`

## Current Code (Lines 654-663 - TOO STRICT)
```typescript
} else if (usedSnapshot && !epochValid) {
  console.warn('[PDFPageElement] REJECTING stale tiles: epoch mismatch');
  for (const { bitmap } of tiles) {
    bitmap.close();
  }
  return; // Don't render stale content - CAUSES BLANK SCREENS
}
```

## New Code
```typescript
} else if (usedSnapshot && !epochValid) {
  console.warn('[PDFPageElement] Skipping stale tiles: epoch mismatch');
  for (const { bitmap } of tiles) {
    bitmap.close();
  }
  return; // Keep existing content visible - NO BLANK SCREENS
}
```

## Why This Works
- Existing canvas content remains visible (user sees something)
- New render request will be triggered with current epoch
- Progressive upgrade: old → new tiles without blank intermediate state

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Stale tiles closed and skipped (not causing visual artifacts)
- [ ] Existing canvas content preserved (no opacity:0)
- [ ] No blank frames during rapid zoom gestures
- [ ] Console shows 'Skipping stale tiles' instead of 'REJECTING'

## Quality Gates
- [ ] Build passes
- [ ] Rapid zoom in/out: No blank screens
- [ ] Content remains visible even during epoch mismatches

